The paper deals with approximation algorithms for optimization problems on geometric intersection graphs, which are graphs whose vertices correspond to geometric objects (such as points or disks) and edges correspond to intersections between these objects. This topic falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM), and the paper also involves algorithmic techniques such as data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between running times and approximation ratios, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
